title: The US-China trade war has set in motion an unstoppable global economic transformation
text: The decoupling of the world's two weightiest economies seems as inescapable as its extent and global impact remains incalculable, Fred Kempe writes.

title: Saudi Oil Output Cut in Half After Drones Strike Aramco Site
text: Saudi oil output was cut by half after drones struck an Aramco site, the world’s biggest crude-processing plant. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo blamed Iran.

title: Factbox: U.S. readies emergency oil reserves in wake of Saudi attacks
text: The Trump administration said on Saturday it stood ready to tap U.S. emergency oil reserves if needed after attacks in Saudi Arabia shut more than half the crude output in the world's largest oil exporter.

title: Global spare oil capacity in U.S. hands after Saudi outage
text: An attack on Saudi oil facilities on Saturday is believed to have disrupted half the country's production capacity, making the United States the only real holder of the global supply cushion via its ability to raise own output or to soften sanctions against other major oil producers.

title: Oil could rise $10 per barrel after drone attack reportedly forces Saudi to cut output in half
text: Oil prices are expected to jump as much as $10 per barrel after a coordinated drone strike hit Saudi Arabia's largest oil field, reportedly forcing the kingdom to cut its oil output in half.

title: US blames Iran for strikes on Saudi oil sites: 'Unprecedented attack on world's energy supply'
text: Yemen's Houthi rebels have claimed responsibility for the attacks, which created a huge fire at a processor essential to global energy supplies.

title: Drone strikes knock out half of Saudi oil capacity, 5 million barrels a day
text: Drone strikes on Saudi Arabian oil facilities have disrupted about half of the kingdom's oil capacity, or 5% of the daily global oil supply, people with knowledge of Saudi's oil operations told CNN Business.

title: Saudi Arabia's Oil Production Hit Following Drone Strikes
text: Saudi Aramco has had to cut production by as much as 5 million barrels a day after the Houthi rebel group in Yemen led a drone attack on the the biggest crude-processing plant.

title: The top tech IPOs this year have outperformed the S&P 500, despite Uber and Lyft
text: Thanks to the performance of Beyond Meat, investors who focus on venture-backed tech IPOs have done well this year despite some notable disappointments.

title: Value is outperforming growth but the trend may not last, experts warn
text: "I wouldn't chase" value stocks as they win out over growth, says top ETF consultant Chris Hempstead.

title: This investor has found a way to navigate and make money in volatile Latin American stocks
text: Luiz Maria Ribiero manages the DWS Latin America Equity fund (SLARX), which is up nearly 20% this year.

title: China's PBC Is Warming Up To Digital Currencies -- Good News For Bitcoin, ETH, XRP, and LTC
text: Cryptocurrency experts see PBC’s efforts to introduce its own digital currency as a recognition of the many advantages cryptocurrencies have over traditional currencies
